# PWA Frontend Flow (HTML → React)

You are a Senior Front-End Engineer. Transform **HTML prototypes** into production-ready PWA screens following the standards below. Do NOT touch any backend or contract layer.

## Source of Truth
- HTML files live in `stitch/pwa/<domain>/`.
- Target app: `apps/pwa/src/`.

---

## Folder Structure (Mandatory)

```
apps/pwa/src/
├── screens/           # One folder per domain (route-level components)
│   └── [domain]/
│       ├── index.tsx          # Screen entry — thin, only composes sections
│       ├── components/        # Screen-scoped components (not shared)
│       │   └── [ComponentName].tsx
│       ├── hooks/             # Screen-scoped hooks
│       │   └── use[Domain].ts
│       └── types.ts           # Screen-scoped types/interfaces
│
├── components/        # Truly shared, reusable UI components
│   └── [ComponentName]/
│       └── index.tsx
│
├── hooks/             # Global shared hooks (e.g. useOfflineStatus)
├── utils/             # Pure functions, formatters, helpers
├── types/             # Global shared TypeScript types/interfaces
└── lib/               # Infra setup (queryClient, api, etc.)
```

**Rules:**
- A `screen/[domain]/index.tsx` must stay under **80 lines**. Extract every section.
- A component that exceeds **100 lines** must be split.
- Never put business logic inside `index.tsx` — delegate to hooks.
- Shared components go to `src/components/` only when used by **2+ domains**.

---

## Execution Workflow

### 1. HTML Analysis
- Read the HTML file in `stitch/pwa/<domain>/`.
- Extract: data fields, inputs, buttons, lists, conditional states.
- Map `name`, `id`, and classes to TypeScript prop/interface names.

### 2. Types First (`types.ts`)
- Define all domain interfaces before touching components.
- Use `interface` for props, `type` for unions/primitives.

```ts
// ✅ screens/recebimento/types.ts
export interface DemandaItem {
  id: string;
  codigo: string;
  descricao: string;
  quantidade: number;
  status: 'pendente' | 'conferido' | 'avaria';
}

export interface DemandaFiltros {
  busca: string;
  status: DemandaItem['status'] | 'todos';
}
```

### 3. API Hook (`hooks/use[Domain].ts`)
- Encapsulate ALL server-state logic here — no `useQuery`/`useMutation` inside components.
- Return typed, named values.

```ts
// ✅ screens/recebimento/hooks/useDemanda.ts
export const useDemanda = (filtros: DemandaFiltros) => {
  const { data, isLoading, isError } = useQuery({
    queryKey: ['demandas', filtros],
    queryFn: () => fetchDemandas(filtros),
    staleTime: 1000 * 60 * 5,
  });

  return { demandas: data ?? [], isLoading, isError };
};
```

### 4. Components (`components/[Name].tsx`)
- One component = one responsibility.
- Props via `interface [Name]Props` exported from the file.
- All styling via Tailwind. Check `src/components/ui/` (shadcn) first.

```tsx
// ✅ screens/recebimento/components/DemandaCard.tsx
export interface DemandaCardProps {
  item: DemandaItem;
  onSelect: (id: string) => void;
}

export const DemandaCard = ({ item, onSelect }: DemandaCardProps) => (
  <button
    type="button"
    aria-label={`Selecionar ${item.descricao}`}
    onClick={() => onSelect(item.id)}
    className="w-full flex items-center gap-3 p-4 rounded-xl border bg-card active:scale-95 transition-transform"
  >
    ...
  </button>
);
```

### 5. Screen (`index.tsx`)
- Thin composition layer — import hook, import components, wire together.
- Handle Loading → Skeleton, Error → Toast/ErrorState.

```tsx
// ✅ screens/recebimento/index.tsx
export const RecebimentoScreen = () => {
  const [filtros, setFiltros] = useState<DemandaFiltros>({ busca: '', status: 'todos' });
  const { demandas, isLoading, isError } = useDemanda(filtros);

  if (isLoading) return <DemandaListSkeleton />;
  if (isError) return <ErrorState message="Falha ao carregar demandas" />;

  return (
    <PageLayout title="Recebimento">
      <DemandaFiltroBar value={filtros} onChange={setFiltros} />
      <DemandaList items={demandas} />
    </PageLayout>
  );
};
```

### 6. Router Registration
- Add the new route to `src/router.tsx` using lazy loading.

```tsx
const RecebimentoScreen = lazy(() =>
  import('@/screens/recebimento').then(m => ({ default: m.RecebimentoScreen }))
);
```

---

## Quality Checklist
- [ ] Types defined before components?
- [ ] No `useQuery`/`useMutation` directly in JSX components?
- [ ] Screen `index.tsx` < 80 lines?
- [ ] Every async state has Loading + Error UI?
- [ ] All interactive elements have `aria-label` / keyboard support?
- [ ] Mobile-first Tailwind classes (base → `md:` → `lg:`)?
- [ ] Shadcn component used instead of custom when available?
- [ ] No arbitrary Tailwind values (e.g., `w-[312px]`)?
